  "description": "This dataset provides microsatellite (SSR) genotyping data for 539 worker\n individuals of the alpine bumblebee Bombus kashmirensis collected from 36\n populations across Qinghai Province, China. The dataset includes three\n files: (1) SSR_genotypes_Bombus_kashmirensis.xlsx, containing\n fragment-length genotypes at multiple SSR loci; (2) SSR_markers_info.xlsx,\n listing locus names, primer sequences, repeat motifs, annealing\n temperatures, and allele size ranges; and (3) Sample_metadata.xlsx,\n providing population codes, sampling site names, geographic coordinates,\n and altitude information. All data are formatted in Microsoft Excel\n (.xlsx). These data can be reused to investigate genetic diversity,\n population structure, and environmental adaptation of B. kashmirensis or\n related bumblebee species. No legal or ethical restrictions apply to the\n reuse of these data.",
  "license": "https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode",
